    "timestamp": "2026-06-11T15:21:18.723Z",
    "tool_use_result": {
      "stdout": "{\"additions\":4,\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nFour agent workflows (`agent-improver`, `junior-dev`, `jira-ticket`, `orchestrator`) end with a \\\"Commit execution log to main\\\" step that does:\\n\\n```\\ngit fetch --depth=1 origin main\\ngit checkout -B main origin/main\\n```\\n\\nThis aborts when the working tree is dirty AND the file in question differs between the dirty version and origin/main. We hit this in run [27352429435](https://github.com/pantageepapa/my-harness/actions/runs/27352429435): Claude was thrashing (29 turns, 8 permission denials) and left `.github/workflows/junior-dev.yml` modified-but-uncommitted; meanwhile a manual commit landed on main with a different edit to the same file. The post-step then refused to switch branches.\\n\\nThe post-step only needs a clean main checkout to drop the execution log (which lives at `/home/runner/work/_temp/claude-execution-output.json`, outside the worktree) and push. Adding `-f` discards orphan working-tree state — anything Claude meant to keep is already on its PR branch.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [ ] Next agent-improver / junior-dev / jira-ticket / orchestrator run completes its log-commit step even after a racing push to main\\n- [ ] No regression in the happy path (clean working tree)\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"changedFiles\":4,\"deletions\":4,\"headRefName\":\"fix/agent-improver-checkout\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"Agent log-commit: force checkout to survive racing main pushes\"}",
      "stderr": "",
      "interrupted": false,
      "isImage": false,
      "noOutputExpected": false
    }
